                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d515">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1115/3961: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">Then in France, to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">St. Jean de Luz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-15T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 15, 1937—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 15—11:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>332. My 323, August 5, 1 p.m.<note n="90" xml:id="d515fn90">Not printed.</note>
                    Cuban Consul Abela here this morning. He says most “Cubans” are really Spanish
                    but born by chance in Cuba and under Cuban laws Cuban citizens. He say his
                    purpose is to send those brought out by us into rebel territory. This latter
                    purpose in my opinion gravely compromises our record of absolute neutrality if
                    Valencia hears and any of the Cubans are of military age. Since the <hi
                        rend="italic">Kane</hi> will probably return from Santander before going to
                    Gijon you have time to consider this new phase.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
